===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|ibex|lang=la}}, 'chamois', from Iberian or Aquitanian; akin to Old Spanish ''bezerro'', 'bull' (mod. ''becerro'' 'yearling').

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'aɪbɛks/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=ibex|pl2=ibexes|pl3=ibices}}

# a type of wild mountain [[goat]] of the genus ''Capra'', such as the species [[Capra ibex]]

